Whatever is so true that it cannot cease to be true, is necessary; and this is the case withvthings that have happened in the Past. God Himself cannot restore lost virginity. The Past is immutably what it is3 and therefore its truth is necessary. If the same thing could happen again, the return of adead man to life would be no miracle. Any singular proposition referring to a fact may be known as eternally ,and therefore necessarily true. Why should we take thought for the future, if we can make the past not to have been?
